            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>So the sandbox is currently just &quot;run this Python code in a container.&quot; The vision is a full workbench for data work. Folder upload is literally your request — accept a ZIP, extract it, figure out what kinds of files are in there, automatically organize into data/, docs/, code/, images/. The auto_organize tool is the smart layer that does the classification and creates the folder structure. For development work, install_package lets agents add new libraries and they stick around across subsequent code runs. git_clone pulls in code repos for analysis. Then data pipeline tools: data_profile gives instant exploratory data analysis, data_clean handles routine cleaning without requiring pandas code, batch_transform applies operations across multiple files, and export_report turns workspace artifacts into a polished final deliverable. There's also hardening work needed — size limits, concurrent access locks, swap limits, that kind of thing — but the core tools are all doable.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
